title: Album Page, "Curious Balcony at Keppelheim", September 18, 1887
medium: Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, below drawing: curious balcony at / Keppelheim / Sept 18th 1887; in upper right corner: (inscribed in circle) 49 / 61.
description: Vertical sheet with small drawing in upper left corner depicting a half-timber structure seen from one side.  The roof is steeply pitched and there are two deep eaves visible.  There is a balcony below a window that is supported from below by large timbers.

tombstone.epitaph:
Album Page, "Curious Balcony at Keppelheim", September 18, 1887.
September 18, 1887. Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-129.
